"In reviewing the recent enforcement action taken by regulators, such as the UK's Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), it becomes plain that simply implementing security technology – or even policies for that matter – is no longer enough. Cath Everett explores how organisations can go about embedding security into the corporate culture. She explores the idea that neither technology nor security policies in and of themselves are enough, but must be backed up with an effective awareness campaign and sound processes and procedures. She also examines how one organisation, Bupa UK, went about doing just that. In reviewing the recent enforcement action taken by regulators, such as the UK's Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), it becomes evident that simply implementing security technology – or even policies for that matter – is no longer enough. Instead, the focus has shifted to training staff in appropriate data-handling techniques to try and ensure that a given data breach does not happen again. This stance was also backed up by management consultancy PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) in its June report entitled ‘Protecting your Business’. 1"
